The paper deals with the problem of steering a team of UAVs equipped with visual sensors to maximize the visibility of a 3D environment. This problem falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO) as it involves controlling multiple agents to achieve a common goal. The use of visual sensors and optimization algorithms also suggests that the paper could be categorized under computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The problem of optimizing the visibility of the environment can also be seen as a control systems problem (cs.SY). Finally, the use of optimization algorithms and machine learning techniques suggests that the paper could also be categorized under machine learning (cs.LG).
